The paper discusses bibliometric-enhanced search facilities for interactive information retrieval, which is a common topic in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Digital Libraries (cs.DL) sub-categories. The paper also mentions citation search, which is relevant to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Security and Privacy (cs.CR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the potential implementation and evaluation of new search services, which could fall under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
